modules.description: Implements path-based routing using string literals to define routes, mapping them to handlers. Works with route lists and dispatch tables, enabling direct association of URL paths to functions. Useful for configuring web servers or client-side routers with readable, declarative path patterns.

Implements path-based routing by matching hierarchical paths against predefined routes, extracting variables and handling exact or prefix matches. Works with lists of routes composed of literal or variable path segments, producing mappings from path components to values. Directly supports configuring web servers or client-side routers with declarative path patterns mapped to handlers.
